  • Constructor Details

    • XmlReader

      public XmlReader(String FILENAME, String type)
      Creates a XmlReader object that fills in this class' properties values based on the type of GameScene you try to create. Those properties are used at the creation of each GameScene.
      Parameters:
      FILENAME - Directory and name of the .xml file that contains the data.
      type - Type of GameScene you try to create.
      See Also:
      • Level
      • Room

    • getRoomFile

      public String getRoomFile(String roomNumber)
      Returns the appropriate room .xml file based on its room number. Note : If the room number doesn't exist a NoSuchFile string is returned.
      Parameters:
      roomNumber - The room's number that refers to the file you try to get.
      Returns:
      the .xml file that matches to the roomNumber parameter.
